-- SocGen stock rises on renewed BNP bid talk: traders
-- 
-- Tue Jan 29, 2008 12:24pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/29/us-socgen-shares-idUSWEB339320080129

 

 PARIS  (Reuters) - Shares in French bank Societe Generale surged more than 9 percent on Tuesday on renewed market talk that rival BNP Paribas could launch a takeover bid for the bank, traders said. 

 Asked about the SocGen bid rumor, BNP Paribas said it had no comment to make. At 9:03 a.m. EST, SocGen stock was up 8.4 percent at 77 euros, bouncing back from a recent sharp decline. BNP shares were up 3.3 percent. "The breakup/bid rumors on SocGen resurface again," one trader said. Traders said they heard talk that BNP could launch a 92 euros a share bid for SocGen. (Reporting by Paris and London newsrooms)